article.headline: Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 99, Texas State 89
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Josh Washington scored 22 points and Texas A&M-Corpus Christi shot 60 percent from the field as the Islanders beat Texas State 99-89 on Thursday night. Texas A&M Corpus Christi (19-5, 10-1 Southland) jumped out to a 20-4 lead and never looked back. The Islanders led 50-41 at halftime. Scooby Johnson added 16 points and seven rebounds for the Islanders. Chris Daniels and Taurean Mitchell had 14 points apiece. Chris Agwumaro led Texas State (8-17, 3-9) with 22 points. Brent Holder came off the bench to contribute 17 and Antwoine Blanchard had 13. Brandon Bush led the Bobcats with six rebounds and five assists. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi won the rebounding contest 38-28. Texas State recorded 48 percent field-goal shooting for the game.
